dy doing the real work. That keeps the rule set simpler and more honest: protect the healthy morning engine, keep only exceptional 19h setups, and avoid redundant filters that add complexity without improving expectancy.\n\n**Decision:**\n- Keep the leading smart-entry recommendation unchanged:\n  - **active hours `[11, 12, 19]`**\n  - **45** threshold for 11h/12h\n  - **55** threshold for 19h\n  - **block `REDUCE_MILD_BEAR` and `BOOST` at 19h**\n  - **drop 20h**\n- Do **not** add a separate midpoint-price exclusion right now, because the current filtered keep-set already avoids churn by construction.\n\n**Next:** On the next P2 heartbeat, test whether a lightweight **reliability \u00d7 edge score gate** can rank borderline 11h/12h trades without harming the strong morning sample.\n\n---\n\n## 2026-04-22 04:59 UTC \u2014 [P1: Copy Intelligence] 04h Reversion Did Not Teach Copy Flow Anything Useful\n\n**Task:** Test whether PM copy flow became more aligned or informative after the clear 04h interruption-and-reversion sequence.\n**Finding:**\n- Both bots are alive and P",
